radiographic_examinations.findings: Interval placement of a right-sided PICC line that appears to terminate in the right atrium; lung volumes are slightly low, but lungs appear better expanded compared to the previous study; less crowding of the pulmonary vasculature and improved bibasilar atelectasis; cardiomediastinal contours are stable; no pleural effusions and no pneumothorax.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Improved bibasilar atelectasis compared to the previous study.
